reviews.title: Poor service performance
reviews.text: After being ignored for over 20 minutes, although the restaurant was little visited, we decided to leave the restaurant again. I can not recommend the restaurant from the service.

reviews.title: B&B URK
reviews.text:
Very well liked.
Friendly staff, great food, great breakfast.
Was there 4 nights due to 3 days congress of Jehovah's Witnesses in Swifterband. 
They also have B&B
Very nice location on the water.
Definitely recommended. 
Marco Verhoeven

reviews.title: Bad
reviews.text: Service spoken in English and rather pricey .when English is already spoken and that in a village like urk then it no longer needs from us

reviews.title: Last visit was much better.
reviews.text: There were already some guests, but it was not very crowded. There were plenty of staff. I was completely ignored for 10 minutes by the service who liked me, but didn't do much else. The Mood was not so pleasant inside, outside it was a bit chilly. I guess I just left. I don't spend money where I don't feel welcome.

reviews.title: For lack of alternatives visited on a Sunday.
reviews.text:
We, 2 couples, were there for dinner on Sunday. There were two fish & chips, one fish soup, one kibbeling and one the gambas. To put it in advance: “the quality had maximum snack level and at an overpriced price”! In addition, the kibbeling and an additionally ordered portion of fries was much too greasy. (in the fish shop quite different below) The side salads were not really well made. The fish soup was quite ok.

One operator (accent) was very polite and friendly, the other apparently lacked desire, which could also be clearly seen in her expression. 

All in all as a conclusion for us, once enough. Too bad, as the location itself is quite nice.

reviews.title: Highly recommended for the fish lover
reviews.text:
Delicious fish eaten. Tasty salmon and fresh eel. If you are in Urk this is a must, but make a reservation. We could only sit inside but at the window that is totally fine even in the summer. 
The children received a lot of attention, a coloring page, happy straws, ice cream with specks. Anything was possible. 
Despite having few staff, very friendly staff. 
Overall highly recommended.
Bad fat over baked kibbeling much residual waste in the bins and too expensive.not worth repeating for us .we were there today with 4 people.

reviews.title: Jammer, Jammer.
reviews.text:
What a disappointment.
We go to Urk for a day to see this picturesque place.
We decide to have lunch at De Kaap.
We won't forget this lunch anytime soon.
The service does not speak Dutch and what is striking is that the serving is chaotic. The waitstaff doesn't know who ordered what. After some inquiries, the ordered dishes end up on the right tables.
We decide to go for a duo of fish (€ 21,50) and order this twice.
What we were served after 15 minutes was terrible.
On the plate we find 2 ‘fillets’ that come right out of the fryer and float in the fat.
We decide to try to get rid of the fillets anyway.
Both fillets (cod and probably plaice) were full of bones. Bones in fish is quite normal but this was not normal. Every bite was a very unpleasant experience. Called the controls to account. Her answer was that they get the fish delivered like this and there is nothing she can do about it. The cook is asked and he confirms that the fish is fried and is far too fatty. He'll do a better job of checking the fillets for bones from now on.
Eventually we left the food and asked for a solution, there was a discount of 50%.
Bad(s) (tourist) restaurant.
What a shame that a restaurant in such a beautiful location drops so many stitches.
Not doing well!
Tip: Try to deliver quality, a restaurant in such a beautiful location should be better.

reviews.title: Great lunch with nice and attentive staff!!
reviews.text: Delicious lunch used (3 courses) Quality food fine. So did the service (although a few people had comments that the ladies had to do it in English). Service very good and attentive. Also active.... Eaters away, immediately clear table and clean well (incl. disinfect). Nice location with beautiful views. Parking also fine. Close and free. With parking disc max 3 hours.  Worth repeating 👍👍👍

reviews.title: Fish with the kids
reviews.text: Super tasty fish eaten with the kids. Price is very reasonable, nice place on the water, restaurant has a cozy atmosphere and friendly staff

reviews.title: Delicious!
reviews.text: I enjoyed a delicious duo flatfish menu together with a friend, it was really delicious! I felt very welcome and the wait staff was top notch and also humorous. This restaurant is really worth a 10+! I love coming back! 😋

tips.body: Dit restaurant vooral niet voorbij lopen!

reviews.title: Top Restaurant
reviews.text:
We have eaten extremely well the owner listened carefully to the wishes 
And is a very fine man. The restaurant was also beautifully decorated with the Christmas decorations. The service was very good and professional.  And now the review the Cooks I give them a grade 10 the food was fantastic really top, we will definitely be back here, with our friends. View grandiose 
The owners will be so proud of this location. 
Kind regards to you
Johan and Jolly van de Berg

reviews.title: Cozy night out with fantastic food in a cozy atmosphere? This is where you go!
reviews.text: Tonight we had dinner in a very quiet restaurant. The restaurant was already in Christmas spirit, cozy and warm. Nice music, country, 60s, all kinds of cozy styles. The playlist of the owner and that created a pleasant atmosphere, you could hear the cook and the hostess singing along, delicious. This cheerfulness automatically skips. The food was great, I had scampi’s, my partner eel, our main course was the Angus steak, what a nice piece of super tender meat, the best fried steak in ages. Dessert: a lady blanche, delicious ice cream with a jug of chocolate. We went out feeling like we had just eaten a little too much. But it was so tasty and cozy. Highly recommended

reviews.title: Lots of really tasty fish
reviews.text: Just really good food. Lots of fish and therefore lots of eel. Otherwise looks very normal and normal service and prices but really good food.

reviews.title: Nice evening.
reviews.text: We spent a nice evening. The food - in our case fish and a sundae - and the magnificent view were more than great. Our waitress, the lady from Austria, guided us superbly through the evening. Thank you very much.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

randomContentList.sponsorDisplayName: Fort Myers – Islands, Beaches and Neighborhoods

tripContent.title: Head to Fort Myers for amazing outdoor adventures
tripContent.description: Seeking adventure on your next vacation? Head to the greater Fort Myers area, where action-packed onshore and offshore activities are yours to enjoy year-round. Water sports, nature parks and wildlife excursions are just some of the highlights on this itinerary that is all about having fun in the sun.

articleContent.title: 3 ways to get from Sydney to the Blue Mountains

seoInfo.metaDescription: Whether you're taking a car, train, or hour-long helicopter tour to get there, the Blue Mountains offer lots to do just beyond Sydney.

articleContent.title: 5 perfect days in New York City

seoInfo.metaDescription: More than 60 million people visit New York City every year, and a huge percentage of them only hit the big sites—Times Square, the Empire State Building, etc. I get it: They’re iconic. But as someone who has lived in this city for more than 30 years, I’m here to tell you that you’re missing out if you don’t mix in some off-the-beaten path locations. Luckily, five days gives you plenty of time to do just that.

articleContent.title: 6 must see things inside Notre Dame Cathedral

seoInfo.metaDescription: Notre Dame is back. Rebuilt in an epic, five-year feat after the catastrophic 2019 fire, Paris’ treasured cathedral is now open and even more spectacular than before. Let me prepare you for the dazzlement that awaits. The light! The colors! The art! Take it from me: you’ll want to spend more than the 35-minute average visit.

reviews.title: Great food, little hospitality!
reviews.text:
Nice location, with the view of the water and dozens of sparrows around you. The food was very tasty, fish board, bread with eel and kibbeling. 
Service is mediocre, little attention, long wait for your food and drink and prices here on Tripadvisor are wrong. 
We missed the hospitality. 

Conclusion: good food, lesser service.

reviews.title: Correct
reviews.text: The restaurant is authentic with a very beautiful view. The dishes are correct and very generous. Nothing great but it was ok

reviews.title: Cozy tent on the water.
reviews.text: Nice tent in a funny village. Sweet girls serving on the sunny terrace in October. It couldn't be better. Tasty lunch of fish species. Not wrong. Beautiful view over the Zuiderzee.

reviews.title: The Cape
reviews.text:
Very tasty food and very friendly service.
The location of the restaurant is beautiful, by the sea.
Recommended.

reviews.title: Must experience
reviews.text: Great ambience, nice friendly service, very tasty food from angus to fish and desserts

reviews.title: A rather gorgeous lunch!
reviews.text: In the very heart of Holland, I mean in the green Noordoostpolder but beneath the magic Zuiderzee, you'll find the jewel-village of Urk! And if you want a really gorgeous fish food in Urk, the must is De Kaap. A cosy, splendid reataurant, where you can find the Vissoep: absolutely divine! The Bordje Kibbeling definitely special! The Belgian Bier LA CHOUFFE, a God's beverage, and the unbelievably gorgeous Sorbet... something you must try! On top of all these great gourmand surprises you'll find there also a blonde, Dutch Siren... full of energy and simpathy and very kind indeed! Martha! We'll never forget You!

reviews.title: very nice restaurant well situated along the boardwalk with great fish dishes
reviews.text:
After having made a walk in the center of the old town of Urk and having passed this restaurant on our way to the memorial we returned to this place to have a lunch. As their specialty is fish we opted for a fish platter and my partner had the fish soup. There is a nice view over the Ysselmeer from inside and they say that this is the best location in town which might certainly be true. 
The food was served after some waiting time as for the lunch hour the restaurant was filled with people and their seating capacity was restricted due to the corona-measures. The quality of the food was excellent and the prices moderate. So a place to recommend if you are in this nice old fishery town which formerly was an island.

photo.caption: view over the Ysselmeer from inside the restaurant
view on the outside of the restaurant along the boardwalk
this is the very nice fish platter with a variety of fish

reviews.title: Lunch with a view
reviews.text: While visiting the beautiful harbor of Urk, we have discovered this nice restaurant, with an awesome view on the sea, from the terrace.  The fish was very good and fresh, for a decent price. Very good lunch, recommended!

reviews.title: Good fish restaurant with singing waiter
reviews.text: Nice fish restaurant that also serves meet. Fantastic view over the see. Very very good fish well prepered. Nice and attentive service.

reviews.title: Charming place and great food!
reviews.text:
Service was friendly and polite, food was excellent and tasty and plenty.  Friendly service and food and view of the sea. Interior was original and charming.
I would recommend plaice for main course. Selection of starters was great.

reviews.title: Nice view, but slow and lousy service
reviews.text: The restaurant was pretty empty, but still the service was slow.  We actually had to ask for our main dish and then the order was wrong on top of it.

reviews.title: Pleasant lunch
reviews.text: The food was good and the décor was very interesting, charming and authentic. Nice sea and harbour view.

reviews.title: Nice view, good service and excellent food
reviews.text: A very nice restaurant on the seaside in the charming village of Urk. Inside by the window or outside table possibilities. Quick service and excellent food. Not a place for the most expensive wines, but a reasonable wine list and a good selection of beer. We had a fish soup for starter and a angus beef for main course. Recommended!

reviews.title: Disastrous service
reviews.text:
We were waiting there for more than 15’ for the waitress to come and take the order
When the order came, it was wrong!
Don’t waste your time and money here

reviews.title: Very good fish and chips
reviews.text: The restaurant is well located with a sea view. We had fish and chips for lunch. It was very good. The restaurant inside is very nice. There are a lot of boats things.

reviews.title: Urk trip
reviews.text: Good food, the only Resto open on eastern day! But a bit pricey. Sitting next to the window with sea view. Good lunch and good trip in Urk.

reviews.title: Friendly, clean
reviews.text:
After a walk around this lovely old island village stopped for a drink.
Friendly staff, clean place, lovely decorated.
As we had a pick nick before we only had some drinks.
Hot chocolate is must have. Nice and hot with a big splash of whip cream.
The food we saw served looked fantastic and people seem to enjoy it very much.
Next visit to Urk we will definitely stop by for lunch or for dinner!

reviews.title: Friendly and customer oriented
reviews.text: Good food. We asked if it would be possible to serve one of the dishes with salad instead of fries and they said yes! Very nice!

reviews.title: Great food for a very reasonable price and very friendly service.
reviews.text: Drinks outside and dinner afterwards inside. Good food, mainly fish and a friendly and smooth service. Rather poor decoration inside though but nice views when seated at the window.

reviews.title: great lunch of fresh fish and eel..
reviews.text: Located on the water in Urk, DeKaap offers fresh seafood well prepared.   We were there for lunch as we toured the water area.    The meal of three different fishes was tasty and well prepared.  My wife had the eel salad and enjoyed it greatly.  The service was very nice and friendly.

reviews.title: So-so
reviews.text: The restaurant offered special meals at a reduced rate for coupons given out by a supermarket chain. We, a party of 4, tried this because reviews were OK. The menu had a lot of lyrical descriptions about the food, and based on those descriptions we expected fairly special courses. This turned out to be disappointing. Appetizers were nothing special. The fish for the main course was deep-fried and very greasy and my rib roast turned out to be a pork chop (not described as such on the menu!) that was a bit overcooked and fairly dry. Dessert choice was icecream with or without fruit (which turned out to be canned fruit). Too bad, since we shall not readily return. In my opinion there is no excuse to serve poor quality, even at discount rates. Service was swift and friendly but, evidently, untrained (our waitress did not recognize the type of fish). The view over the lake is very nice.

reviews.title: Nice, friendly bistro
reviews.text: Small nice friendly bistro in a small town, beautiful sight through the window and terrace. Friendly and helpful service, not expensive compared to some other bistro/ cafe. Enjoined the stay and drinks

mgmtResponse.text:
Dear mister Richard V.,

Thank you for the time and the compliments about the girls who are working in the restaurant.
I always enjoy it, when they are getting compliments because they are a big treasure for our company and have heart for it.
Further more there where 2 girls who were a little inexperienced, but did there very best and more than that.

As we see on your review, you where here on Easter sunday 2017. (16/04/2017)
The day that the Kaap is the only company on Urk that is open. (in a radius of 20 km)
That explains the many people who are there, but there where also a lott of regular guests.

Cold and bad food:
Dear mister Richard, we will gladly repay you for your inconvinience of cold food and bad food.
We have just some questions:
1. Where you sitting inside or outside on the terras? Because there was a lott of wind that day and the food can get cold in the wind.
2. What did you order? Because some dishes are served cold.
3. You can send this to info@restaurantdekaap.nl and we solve your problem.
4. Maybe the food wasn't what you thought of it.

Expensive: 
You think we are way to expensive and offcourse is this your personal opinion.
We think that we have low prices when you compare us to other restaurants.
When you compare us to a snackbar than we're more expensieve.
This is because you're paying for the setting on the water, the lovely girls who give you much attention with taking, bringing and cleaning the table.
The girls and boys who are running, cleaning and cooking in the kitchen.
The furniture, rent, taxes and way more things.

How it Looks:
Thank you for the compliment that it looks nice.
We just painted and put in another floor.
Also the toilets were just restyled and were finished om 04/04/2017.

It Ducks: We think you mean something else and we always respect our guests personal opinion. We think something else!!

As for the boss: I think you're absolutly right about this! 
There is only one thing, he was not in the Bahamas but on his bed at home on Urk (next to the company) with pressure on his chest from his work.
For your information: He openend that day alone at ± 9:00 and at 12:00 o'clock the girls where there to help him.
He also texted 1 of the girls and 1 chef, that he would lay down and take some Ibuprufen 600 because off his discomfort and when it was neccesary they must call hem right away.
Arround 16:00 he was back to help because the girls called him and he stayed there untill all of the staff had eaten and could sit down to take some well deserved rest.

Nobody cares whats happening inside:
Again thats your opinion. Maybe it looks like that, but it doesn't. 
The whole staff was asked for the restyling from the Kaap from the cleaner to the owner.
Everybody is working very hard over there to make this company a succes.

Also this reply to your review says that we're not involved at all.

On the last note we will say that we hope to see you again and hope to prove that this opinion was a mistake on his own.
Because every review we learn from our guests to get better.

Dear mister Richard V., you're always welcome at the Kaap and we hope you still had a very nice Easter and holiday in the Netherlands.

You can always reach us for hints or directions on: info@restaurantdekaap.nl 

Best regards from a beautifull company,

Klaas Pieter Hakvoort

Hello and goodafternoon Mrs. Rumi K.,

First, we wish you a beautifull 2017 in good health and much luck.

We thank you for taking the time to write a review on Tripadvisor about De Kaap.

reviews.title: A beautiful view and a nice meal.
reviews.text: We had fish.  The dish with three fish was too much, but delicious.  The server was very friendly, helpful and pleasant.  The view was phenomenal.  We were there during one of the hot days in August and it was busy outside, not inside.  It really was worth a visit. There is parking at the Westkade at Urk and walking from there is easy.

photo.caption: The view on a hot day
Another view over the IJselmeer showing from where we sat

reviews.title: Average restaurant on great location
reviews.text:
Me and my girlfriend went for diner to this restaurant a Saturday evening. The weather was nice, but we decided to eat inside. The view from the inside to the IJsselmeer is just as lovely as from the terrace, they paid attention to make sure nothing blocks the sight. Many people strolling by on the boulevard, which makes it never boring. A lot of German tourists were around, perhaps they had holiday.
The food was nice, I would give it an average. My starter was a traditional fish soup from Urk, and it was absolutely delicious.  Main course involved three types of fried fish filet, two of which were cod and plaice. It was served with ravigotte sauce. At the side we had baked potatowedges, chips and asparagus. Although my fish portion was rather small, the taste left nothing to be desired. My desert was a sorbet with fresh fruits and strawberry ice, which was good. For beer lovers like me, they offer the entire collection of La Chouffe special beers. 
Location: 8.5   Quality: 7   Value for money: 5    Occupation: 7.5    Crew: 7

mgmtResponse.text:
Geachte heer Machiel,

Dank u voor uw warme woorden, dit doet ons altijd heel veel deugd in onze zoektocht om beter te worden.

De 3 vissoorten waren: Kabeljauwfilet, Heekfilet (een soort van neefje van de kabeljauw, alleen wat steviger qua bouw) en Scholfilet.
Normaal bakken wij de vis op een Urker wijze. Eerst in de olie (dichtschroeien) , daarna afwerken met roomboter.
Ik zal dit punt opnemen met de keukenbrigade van de bewuste zaterdagavond.

Inmiddels werken wij aan een nieuwe menukaart, om na het seizoen een ruimere keus in smaken te kunnen aanbieden.
De aperges waren schorseneren (lijken sprekend op elkaar), hier krijgen wij veel complimenten over. Waarschijnlijk omdat het een "vergeten" groente is en ietsjes zoeter van smaak dan de asperge.

Er is bewust voor de brouwerij van Duvel-Moorgat gekozen ( La CHouffe serie ), omdat die anders zijn dan de gesettelde biersoorten.
Dank u voor de bevestiging voor deze keus en dat dit een "goede" keus is geweest.

Nogmaals onze dank voor uw review en mocht u tips of andere aanwijzingen voor ons hebben, kunt u ons altijd bereiken op: info@restaurantdekaap.nl 
Wij willen altijd beter worden en zijn dan ook zeer verheugd als gasten hun mening hierover geven en hierin willen bijdragen.

Met een vriendelijke groet vanaf een zonnig Urk,

De Kaap
Crew

reviews.title: A light dinner in Urk
reviews.text:
Driving around through the polder I decided to eat an early dinner in Urk. I landed at the Kaap near the lighthouse and went to this fish restaurant with view to the lake/sea side.
There is a little terrace just before the entrance of the restaurant with a nice view over the port and sea. This early evening the temperature was to low to enjoy a meal in the open ait so I went into the restaurant and was lucky to get the last table at the window. I ordered a " Urker fish soup 5/5, a 2 fillet plate 4/5 and a Haselino dessert 4/5. The service was friendly and flexible, the ambiance a little old fashioned but taking in account all it was a pleasant moment. The choices of fish are quite limited and Victoria brass isn' t really a fish belonging to Urk nor the North Sea!

reviews.title: Organized a group of 30 in 1hour
reviews.text:
We were sailing with 6 yachts and 30 people. After checking many restaurants in Urk this was the only one to manage the people and to serve some good steak and fish to us.
We were lucky to find this place via Tripadvisor!
And they are a great team. Very Friendly and welcoming.

And the price was fair enough. 30€ each for food and drinks!

Thumbs up!

reviews.title: A fantasticview, with very good fish food and lovely service
reviews.text: We arrived in Urk on a quite Sunday, found this little gem open. We got in it was warm and cosy, we got a table by the window with a fantastic viewover Ijsselmeer. Windy outside, but warm inside. The waitresses were lovely even in their broken English. The food was amazing..a tasty masheoom soup as a starter And a huge portion of double fish with all possible side dishes that we shared. Good beer...and a final suprise when the bill arrived: very good value for money! what more can we ask from life? And the village is lovely!

reviews.title: Not too bad fish restaurant.
reviews.text:
On a great spot in this authentic village you'll find this fish restaurant. 
Worth the money. Super fresh! The Way they cook, not my style, but it is not bad ! As I said super fresh ! And plenty. Just visit.

photo.caption: Just in the bottom of this lighthouse you will find the place

reviews.title: Worst Ever !
reviews.text:
Admitting that I visited this restaurant in my Pre-Tripadvisor life I was reminded by the absolute terrible way we got treated at this restaurant.  Everything  that could go wrong, Went wrong !

The expiry date of the drinks was months overdue, which was replaced by a drink that was months overdue !  ( I mean, come on ! )
There was a Fly in my soup !
Our Salad, ordered without shrimp,  had loads of.. shrimp !
The hot chocolate for our 5 y.o  was piping hot, she could have burned herself.
 But the worst part was that our complaints to the owner were shrugged away with the remark that sometimes life is not fair… and he went off.  When he presented the bill without any scruples I cynically gave him a big tip and told him to be Very Very pleased with his service. He said that to compensate my youngest could have an Ice cream, But then he wanted 2 scoops, he started to stutter that one should be enough. 

I DO HOPE that since my visit there is another owner, or new management, and someone will write a good review for him.  

I can’t, because I will not go back again… Ever.

PS. My date of visit was not Oktober 2013, but August 2010

reviews.title: A splendid view on the IJsselmeer
reviews.text: Visrestaurant De Kaap is on the waterfront of the village of Urk, and offers a marvellous view on the IJsselmeer (formerly: "Zuiderzee") and the dyke of the Oost Flevoland polder. With good weather, you may look as far as Lelystad (TV tower) and Enkhuizen on the Noord-Holland side of the lake. The restaurant has a little terrace that is well protected against the wind, which mostly blows from the Southwest. We only came for drinks, but were struck by the very friendly service of the attentive staff. Not unimportantly - the restaurant is open on Sunday afternoon and evening, which is quite remarkable as most inhabitants of Urk will only visit one of their many churches on Sundays.
